Washington22 contributions
Don’t bring your dog! Not allowed
Oct 2023 • Couples
Don’t bring a dog here, and don’t visit unless you have run out of other things to do in Barcelona. We read some information online, that left us with the impression you could walk a dog in parts of this park. That is one of the main reasons we decided to go. It is a challenging location to get to. We paid $20 euros for a cab, who dropped us off in the totally wrong spot. Then, we had to ask wonderfully kind locals how to find this Parc. They walked us there, and showed us the entry. We were excited to have finally found it! As soon as the two men worked at the entry saw our dog, they said we could not come in. They told us we could only walk the park alone without the dog. When we asked to take a peek at the park, they said we had to pay the fee, about 2 euros just before closing. One of us paid to go in, while the other waited outside with our puppy. The grounds seemed rather worn, we kept it quick, were inside just a few minutes, and then departed. Would only recommend going if you have a lot of extra time, and maybe try to go on the day the entry to the park is free, although maybe it is more crowded then?

Written October 14, 2023

Tim G
5 contributions
Cool maze
Sep 2023 • Couples
The park is quite easy to get to on the metro. About a 10 min walk from Mundet on L3 the green line. The park is pretty with a lot of shade. The highlight is the Labyrinth. It is the real deal. We did the maze when the park opened up at 10 am. It was pretty confusing getting to the center and even worse trying to find our way out. Some of the maze has been replanted in the last year or two which made it a bit easier. Don’t do this if you are claustrophobic.
Written September 23, 2023

You might be able to just go. We went in the end of April and it was not crowded at all. There were people filming a movie at the time, not sure if they reserved a spot. Admission is very inexpensive, a few euro, we went on a Wednesday and did not have to pay. There is a little bit of a walk from the metro so be prepared for that. There is a reviewer that gave really good directions sometime in 2018 that we followed. It is an informal park and I bet you should have free run of it (depending on the size of your group), if you want to do vows by the ponds, or sculptures, or the maze, or flowers etc. it should be very nice area. This is based on my experience just informally visiting though, so I can't guarantee any of it... Also, congrats!
